                },
                {
                  "title": "Agreement",
                  "customClass": "overflow-auto",
                  "collapsible": false,
                  "hideLabel": true,
                  "key": "agreement",
                  "attributes": {
                    "style": "max-height: 200px"
                  },
                  "type": "panel",
                  "label": "Agreement",
                  "input": false,
                  "tableView": false,
                  "components": [
                    {
                      "label": "Text Area",
                      "widget": "",
                      "applyMaskOn": "change",
                      "autoExpand": false,
                      "hideLabel": true,
                      "disabled": true,
                      "tableView": true,
                      "defaultValue": "DESIGNATION AGREEMENT BETWEEN\n\nHis Majesty the King in Right of the Province of British Columbia,\nas represented by the Minister of Post-Secondary Education and Future Skills\n(the “Province”)\n\nAND\n\nthe Institution \n\n\nWHEREAS: \nA.\tThe Province is responsible for the administration of: \n    •  the Canada Student Financial Assistance Program in accordance with agreements under the Canada Student Loan Act, R.S.C. 1985, c. S-23 and Canada Student Financial Assistance Act, S.C. 1994, c. 28; and \n    •\tthe British Columbia Student Assistance Program (“StudentAid BC”) authorized by British Columbia OIC 1252/2000;\nB.\tStudentAid BC financial assistance is only available to students enrolled in StudentAid BC approved programs at institutions that hold a designation from StudentAid BC for the purpose of student financial assistance (“StudentAid BC Designation”); \nC.\tThe Province designates institutions with StudentAid BC Designation in accordance with the Canada Student Financial Assistance Act, the Canada Student Financial Assistance Regulations, the Pan- Canadian Designation Policy Framework, and the StudentAid BC Policy Manual; and,\nD. The Institution has applied for StudentAid BC Designation. \n\nThe Province and the Institution (together, “the Parties” or individually, a “Party”) agree as follows: \n\n1.0\tDefined Terms \n\n1.1\tDefinitions for terms used in this Agreement are as follows: \n    a)\t“Agreement” means this Designation Agreement and all attached Schedules; \n    b) “Business Day” means a day, other than a Saturday or Sunday, on which Provincial government offices are open for normal business in British Columbia; \n    c)\t“Designated Institution” has the same definition as in the StudentAid BC Policy Manual; and\n    d) “Institution Staff” means any individual acting on behalf of the Institution. This includes, but is     not limited to, employees, recruiters, contractors, and agents. \n\n2.0 Institution acknowledgements \n\n2.1 The Institution acknowledges that: \n    a)\tDesignated Institutions play a central role in ensuring students succeed, and ensuring students improve their overall employability;\n    b) Funding under student financial assistance programs is provided to assist students, not institutions; and, \n    c)\tProtecting the interests of students and taxpayers is the paramount consideration for StudentAid BC Designation.\n\n3.0 Institution responsibilities  \n\n3.1\tThe Institution must do the following: \n    a)\tComply with all requirements of institutions in the StudentAid BC Policy Manual, as amended from time to time, which is available on the StudentAid BC website, including: \n        i.\tThe Institution must ensure Institution Staff do not complete, create, or access applications,  agreements and systems for student financial assistance on a student’s behalf (including but not limited to, student dashboard, the Student Information Management system (SIMS), BC Services Card, the National Student Loans Service Centre portal, or the Master Student Financial Assistance Agreement);\n        ii.\tThe Institution must inform students of their obligation to repay their student loans and the repercussions of defaulting on their student loans before a student signs their Master Student Financial Assistance Agreement;\n        iii. Before the Institution requests that StudentAid BC remit all or a portion of a student’s financial assistance directly to the Institution, the Institution must inform the student of StudentAid BC’s Direct Tuition Remittance Policy and must ensure that the student agrees before the student signs their Master Student Financial Assistance Agreement;\n        iv. When entering programs in SIMS, or changing any characteristics of previously approved programs (such as changes to tuition, program dates, breaks etc.), the Institution must accurately report to StudentAid BC information describing each program of study as approved by the governing body overseeing the delivery of the program, and/or the operation of the Institution;\n        v.\tThe Institution must ensure the responsibilities of the Eligibility Signing Officer and the Enrollment Signing Officer referred to in Schedule A are not carried out by the same employee; \n        vi. The Institution must maintain up to date records for all Institution Staff, including access authorization for current Institution Staff and disabling system access for former Institution Staff; and\n        vii. The Institution must accurately report Confirmation of Enrolment for StudentAid BC funded students and notify StudentAid BC within the timelines specified in the StudentAid BC Policy Manual of any student who fails to meet attendance criteria for full-time studies or withdraws from their studies.\n    b) Comply with all requirements on institutions, in the SIMS Instructional Guide, as amended from time to time, which is available on the StudentAid BC website; \n    c)\tProvide complete and accurate information in the Signing Officers Information form, attached to this Agreement as Schedule A, and provide the Province at least 30 days’ written notice of any changes to the information in Schedule A;\n    d) Comply with the Information Sharing Agreement attached to this Agreement as Schedule B;\n    e)\tCooperate with reviews under section 5.1 of this Agreement; and,\n    f) Comply with all applicable laws.\n\n4.0\tTerm \n\n4.1\tThis Agreement takes effect on the date the Province provides approval of the Agreement in SIMS, granting or renewing the Institution’s StudentAid BC Designation, and will remain in effect until renewed in accordance with section 4.2, or terminated in accordance with section 4.3 or 4.4. \n4.2\tInstitutions must request to renew the Agreement every year on or before the date specified in the StudentAid BC Policy Manual. The Province may elect to renew the Agreement with the Institution at the Province’s sole discretion. \n4.3 This Agreement is terminated on the date the Province terminates the Institution’s StudentAid BC Designation. \n4.4 The Institution may voluntarily terminate its StudentAid BC Designation on no less than 90 days’ written notice to the Province. Where an institution gives such notice, this Agreement terminates on the effective date given in the notice, or 90 days after notice is given, whichever is later.\n\n5.0 Compliance Review and Monitoring \n\n5.1 At any time, the Province may review the Institution for compliance with this Agreement, including by: \n    a)\tMonitoring of the Institution;\n    b) Requiring the Institution to provide information or reports to the Province; and,\n    c)\tIf the Institution holds a certificate under the Private Training Act, SBC 2015 c 5, conducting an inspection under that Act. \n5.2 If the Province in its sole discretion determines the Institution is not in compliance with this Agreement the Province may take actions including some or all of the following: \n    a)\tIssuing guidance or warnings to the Institution, including directions to take or cease an action by a deadline;\n    b) Limiting or refusing to provide financial assistance to students registered in some or all of the programs or courses at the Institution; \n    c)\tCeasing to provide student financial assistance directly to the Institution; \n    d) Suspending the Institution’s StudentAid BC Designation; or\n    e)\tTerminating the Institution’s StudentAid BC Designation.\n5.3 For certainty, nothing in this Agreement limits the Province’s authority to terminate the Institution’s StudentAid BC Designation at any time in its sole discretion. \n\t\n6.0 Notice\n\n6.1 Any notice contemplated by this Agreement must be given: \n    a)\tby email to:\n        i.\tThe Province at <a href=mailto:designat@gov.bc.ca>designat@gov.bc.ca</a>; \n        ii.\tThe Institution’s email as listed in the institution profile on the StudentAid BC Partner Portal;     \n    b) by prepaid registered mail to the Province at: Attn: Executive Director of StudentAid BC, Ministry of Post-Secondary Education and Future Skills, PO Box 9173, Stn Prov Govt, Victoria BC V8W 9H7.\n 6.2 Either Party may provide a substitute email or address for the purpose of section 6.1 on no less than 30 days’ written notice to the other Party.\n6.3 Any notice given under this Agreement will be deemed to have been received by the other Party one Business Day after transmission if it is emailed and two Business Days after it is mailed if it is sent by prepaid registered mail.\n\n7.0\tGeneral\n\n7.1 This Agreement supersedes any previous agreement between the Parties with respect to the subject matter of this Agreement. \n7.2 This Agreement is not assignable or transferrable by the Institution. \n",
                      "persistent": false,
                      "validateWhenHidden": false,
